						               													<description>Your application for ZooLabs has been accepted! You are now one of the candidates to work on a revolutionary study that, through labyrinth experiments, will teach mice to help people escape from natural disasters. On your first day at the lab, you are introduced to your new little friend, and together, you will discover new possibilities for rat intelligence.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Mouse Maze, players represent young scientists working on various experiments, building the best mouse maze to maximize the mouse's path, trying to get through the most cheese and candy (positive points) while avoiding or closing the mousetraps (negative points).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It&amp;rsquo;s a flip and write game in which the players draw the walls of the maze, but it's the opponent who will trace the path (and of course, he&amp;rsquo;ll make the worst route possible). In each turn, one card is flipped to determine which kind of walls the players can draw, some of them including more cheese, candies, or new mousetraps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has a campaign with 30 exciting episodes (split into 10 chapters) that can be played by 1 to 4 players. New rules, objectives and game elements are introduced with each episode, giving players new choices and strategies (without destroying any components). For players who do not want to experience the campaign, each episode can also be played independently of the campaign and out of order, as well as increasing the number of possible players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That's 30 games in one, and you can choose the best one for you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
